your son back,

508
00:26:40,182 --> 00:26:41,725
you know what you
have to do.

509
00:26:41,767 --> 00:26:43,394
I know what you
want me to do...

510
00:26:45,020 --> 00:26:46,604
and I won't do it.

511
00:26:46,646 --> 00:26:48,274
I'm not gonna kill you.

512
00:26:48,315 --> 00:26:50,650
No matter
what you do,

513
00:26:50,692 --> 00:26:53,946
that is never
going to happen.

514
00:26:53,987 --> 00:26:55,406
Never say never.

515
00:26:57,157 --> 00:26:59,326
[Grunting]

516
00:27:22,558 --> 00:27:24,642
You said nothing
ever really dies?

517
00:27:28,021 --> 00:27:30,983
You're going to.

518
00:27:31,024 --> 00:27:33,068
Do svidaniya,
Konstantin.

519
00:27:33,110 --> 00:27:34,487
[Clicks]

520
00:27:34,528 --> 00:27:35,779
Heh.

521
00:27:35,821 --> 00:27:37,114
[Click, click]

522
00:27:37,156 --> 00:27:38,865
My men overheard
your conversation

523
00:27:38,907 --> 00:27:42,702
with that traitor
Knyazev.

524
00:27:42,744 --> 00:27:45,331
[Spits]

525
00:27:45,372 --> 00:27:48,417
The boat he's arranging
will be here soon.

526
00:27:48,459 --> 00:27:49,751
Agh.

527
00:27:49,793 --> 00:27:53,255
I don't have to
kill you, Oliver Queen.

528
00:27:53,297 --> 00:27:57,050
Agh!

529
00:27:57,092 --> 00:27:59,637
Only need to make sure
you never get on that boat.

530
00:28:04,057 --> 00:28:05,017
[Sizzling]

531
00:28:05,058 --> 00:28:06,226
Aah! Argh!

532
00:28:38,551 --> 00:28:40,260
[Canary cries]

533
00:28:42,012 --> 00:28:44,181
[Black Siren
groaning]

534
00:28:50,770 --> 00:28:54,400
You thought you could
replace me?

535
00:28:54,441 --> 00:28:56,860
Ha ha ha!

536
00:28:56,902 --> 00:28:58,278
That's cute.

537
00:28:58,320 --> 00:28:59,488
Unh!

538
00:29:01,114 --> 00:29:02,616
You didn't have
to do that.

539
00:29:02,658 --> 00:29:06,745
Oh, I did
for so many reasons.

540
00:29:06,786 --> 00:29:08,914
Oliver, do you copy?

541
00:29:08,955 --> 00:29:10,624
Are you sure you can't
defuse these bombs?

542
00:29:10,666 --> 00:29:12,251
Well, I can
with my equipment
back in Star City,

543
00:29:12,292 --> 00:29:13,793
but with this
teeny, tiny,
little tablet,

544
00:29:13,835 --> 00:29:15,212
all I can do is try
and locate the trigger.

545
00:29:15,254 --> 00:29:16,213
Thea: OK, but you can
try, right?

546
00:29:16,255 --> 00:29:17,631
Yeah, I can try.

547
00:29:17,673 --> 00:29:18,798
OK. Good. You do that,
and then, Curtis,

548
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:20,259
you just...you work
on the comms, OK?

549
00:29:20,300 --> 00:29:22,761
-How?
-I don't know.

550
00:29:22,802 --> 00:29:24,137
You're the genius,
all right, you both are,

551
00:29:24,179 --> 00:29:26,139
so we need you to do this,

552
00:29:26,181 --> 00:29:28,267
so you guys just got to
both do this right now.

553
00:29:45,825 --> 00:29:47,703
There's the killer
that I know and love.

554
00:29:50,956 --> 00:29:52,832
Aah!

555
00:29:55,628 --> 00:29:58,088
Maybe you're stronger
with that hood of yours.

556
00:29:59,256 --> 00:30:01,508
Tell me
where my son is!

557
00:30:32,164 --> 00:30:34,792
Pain's fascinating,
isn't it?

558
00:30:34,833 --> 00:30:37,085
I told you I was
gonna make sure

559
00:30:37,127 --> 00:30:38,837
that you were
dead this time.

560
00:30:45,177 --> 00:30:46,928
Adrian: Do it, Oliver.

561
00:30:46,970 --> 00:30:48,305
You know you
want to.

562
00:30:48,347 --> 00:30:49,807
Yeah, OK.
Adrian, tell me.

563
00:30:49,848 --> 00:30:52,351
Tell me where my son is!

564
00:30:52,392 --> 00:30:53,477
Never.

565
00:30:56,146 --> 00:30:57,981
[Watch beeping]

566
00:30:58,023 --> 00:30:59,983
You're not going to
make the boat.

567
00:31:00,025 --> 00:31:01,652
[Grunts]

568
00:31:01,694 --> 00:31:03,987
This island will
remain your prison...

569
00:31:04,029 --> 00:31:05,322
[Coughs]

570
00:31:05,364 --> 00:31:06,615
forever.

571
00:31:09,576 --> 00:31:10,994
[Neck snaps]

572
00:31:16,542 --> 00:31:17,584
[Swords clanging]

573
00:31:17,626 --> 00:31:18,960
[Punches landing]

574
00:31:20,295 --> 00:31:21,963
Adrian: It's all over

575
00:31:22,005 --> 00:31:24,257
but only if you do it.

576
00:31:24,299 --> 00:31:25,843
Do it, Oliver,

577
00:31:25,884 --> 00:31:27,135
and show everyone,

578
00:31:27,177 --> 00:31:29,388
show yourself
who you really are.

579
00:31:34,727 --> 00:31:35,977
No!

580
00:31:39,481 --> 00:31:40,733
[Bullet clatters]

581
00:31:40,774 --> 00:31:42,942
[Adrian gasping]

582
00:31:49,324 --> 00:31:51,827
That's who I was.

583
00:31:51,869 --> 00:31:56,373
That's who I was
before!

584
00:31:56,415 --> 00:31:58,250
It's not who
I am now.

585
00:31:59,918 --> 00:32:03,255
You can blame me for
your father's death

586
00:32:03,296 --> 00:32:06,592
for the rest
of your life.

587
00:32:06,633 --> 00:32:09,928
I am done blaming
myself for mine.

588
00:32:12,723 --> 00:32:14,558
I knew it would come to this.

589
00:32:19,479 --> 00:32:21,690
Your son is dead,
Oliver.

590
00:32:43,169 --> 00:32:46,423
I don't believe you

591
00:32:46,465 --> 00:32:50,051
because you're
a liar.

592
00:32:50,093 --> 00:32:53,513
You're lying to me
to manipulate me

593
00:32:53,555 --> 00:32:57,309
into doing
what you want,

594
00:32:57,350 --> 00:33:00,061
but, Adrian, here's
the thing.

595
00:33:00,103 --> 00:33:01,980
If you are
telling the truth...

596
00:33:04,316 --> 00:33:07,569
if you killed
my son,

597
00:33:07,611 --> 00:33:12,783
I am never going to
be the person
you want me to be.

598
00:33:15,243 --> 00:33:16,662
Not ever.

599
00:33:20,624 --> 00:33:22,125
[Felicity on comms:]
<i>Oliver?</i>

600
00:33:22,167 --> 00:33:24,962
-<i>Oliver, do you copy?</i>
-Felicity?

601
00:33:25,003 --> 00:33:26,338
You can't kill Chase.
Did you hear me?

602
00:33:26,379 --> 00:33:27,798
What are you
talking about?

603
00:33:27,840 --> 00:33:30,133
He's rigged
the entire island
with explosives.

604
00:33:30,175 --> 00:33:32,010
They're remotely
linked to some sort
of dead man's switch.

605
00:33:32,051 --> 00:33:34,471
If he dies, it detonates
all the devices.

606
00:33:34,513 --> 00:33:36,264
He wants you
to kill him

607
00:33:36,306 --> 00:33:38,224
so it kills all of us.

608
00:33:43,939 --> 00:33:45,774
<i>Oliver!</i>

609
00:33:45,816 --> 00:33:46,900
Oliver, are you OK?

610
00:33:46,942 --> 00:33:49,569
It's OK. I'm fine.

611
00:33:49,611 --> 00:33:50,821
John, you need to get
to the plane

612
00:33:50,863 --> 00:33:52,071
and make sure that
everyone's safe.

613
00:33:52,113 --> 00:33:53,281
Felicity can talk you in.

614
00:33:53,323 --> 00:33:54,491
Oliver, what
the hell is
going on?

615
00:33:54,533 --> 00:33:55,701
Chase has put
explosive charges

616
00:33:55,742 --> 00:33:57,035
all over the island.

617
00:33:57,076 --> 00:33:58,370
You need to get
to the plane,

618
00:33:58,411 --> 00:34:00,163
and you leave
when you get there.

619
00:34:00,205 --> 00:34:01,414
What are you gonna
be doing?

620
00:34:01,456 --> 00:34:03,416
I'm going after my son.

621
00:34:03,458 --> 00:34:05,335
What if Chase is
telling the truth?

622
00:34:05,377 --> 00:34:08,421
I don't believe him.
I can't believe him,

623
00:34:08,463 --> 00:34:12,050
but either way,
Adrian Chase is not
getting off this island.

624
00:34:57,178 --> 00:34:58,471
[Boat engine starts]

625
00:35:17,741 --> 00:35:19,325
Where's William?

626
00:35:19,367 --> 00:35:20,201
Ehh.

627
00:35:22,203 --> 00:35:24,372
[Panting]

628
00:35:41,014 --> 00:35:42,515
[Speaks Chinese]

629
00:35:57,072 --> 00:35:58,531
Where...

630
00:35:58,573 --> 00:36:00,283
is...

631
00:36:00,325 --> 00:36:02,285
William?

632
00:36:02,327 --> 00:36:03,578
You really love that kid,
don't you?

633
00:36:03,620 --> 00:36:04,955
Adrian!

634
00:36:09,584 --> 00:36:10,752
[Engine stops]

635
00:36:14,422 --> 00:36:17,634
[Exhales]

636
00:36:17,676 --> 00:36:19,385
For an absentee father,

637
00:36:19,427 --> 00:36:22,055
your devotion
is impressive.

638
00:36:22,097 --> 00:36:23,515
You're worried
about your kid

639
00:36:23,556 --> 00:36:25,017
when everyone else
that you care about's

640
00:36:25,058 --> 00:36:27,644
on an island about
to get blown up
sky high.

641
00:36:27,686 --> 00:36:31,773
My friends and my team
can take care
of themselves.

642
00:36:31,815 --> 00:36:35,443
By using my plane
to escape, right?

643
00:36:35,485 --> 00:36:37,236
John: I can't start
the engine.

644
00:36:37,278 --> 00:36:39,072
Curtis: John's right.
There's definitely
something wrong.

645
00:36:39,114 --> 00:36:41,116
With the plane
or the pilot...
no offense.

646
00:36:41,158 --> 00:36:42,826
John: None taken.
I'm no ace,

647
00:36:42,868 --> 00:36:44,243
but I know how
to start a plane.

648
00:36:44,285 --> 00:36:45,787
Whatever this was,
it's not pilot error.

649
00:36:45,829 --> 00:36:47,497
Slade: Either way, we're
not going anywhere

650
00:36:47,539 --> 00:36:50,208
without Oliver
or his son.

651
00:36:50,249 --> 00:36:52,585
Actually, we're not
going anywhere
at all.

652
00:36:52,627 --> 00:36:54,253
I found this 10 feet
from the wing.

653
00:36:54,295 --> 00:36:56,297
Please don't tell me
that's what I think it is.

654
00:36:56,339 --> 00:36:58,675
Depends on if you think
that's an on-wing
hydraulic system.

655
00:36:58,717 --> 00:36:59,843
Dinah:
Can we repair it?

656
00:36:59,885 --> 00:37:01,427
With what tools?

657
00:37:01,469 --> 00:37:03,055
So we're stuck here.
Is that what you're
saying?

658
00:37:03,096 --> 00:37:05,015
We have to tell Oliver now.

659
00:37:06,766 --> 00:37:09,519
[Felicity on comms:]
<i>Oliver, do you copy?</i>

660
00:37:09,561 --> 00:37:10,812
I'm here.

661
00:37:10,854 --> 00:37:11,980
Chase sabotaged
the plane.

662
00:37:12,022 --> 00:37:13,148
We can't get
off the island.

663
00:37:13,190 --> 00:37:14,315
There's an ARGUS
supply ship

664
00:37:14,357 --> 00:37:15,567
on the eastern shore.

665
00:37:15,608 --> 00:37:16,860
That's on the other side
of the island.

666
00:37:16,902 --> 00:37:18,195
Slade knows where it is.
Go now!

667
00:37:18,236 --> 00:37:19,696
They'll never
make it in time.

668
00:37:19,738 --> 00:37:22,281
Besides, we're not
finished here.

669
00:37:22,323 --> 00:37:24,076
Oh!

670
00:37:24,117 --> 00:37:26,036
Don't do that.

671
00:37:26,078 --> 00:37:27,787
Even if you had
a shot,

672
00:37:27,829 --> 00:37:31,290
you've already
told me that you
wouldn't kill me,

673
00:37:31,332 --> 00:37:34,044
or have circumstances
finally changed?

674
00:37:36,421 --> 00:37:41,093
If I die, everyone
you care about dies

675
00:37:41,134 --> 00:37:43,970
except your son,

676
00:37:44,012 --> 00:37:47,140
but if you don't
kill me,

677
00:37:47,182 --> 00:37:49,475
I kill him.

678
00:37:49,517 --> 00:37:51,103
You son of a bitch.

679
00:37:51,144 --> 00:37:53,980
William...

680
00:37:54,022 --> 00:37:56,691
or everyone else.

681
00:37:56,733 --> 00:37:58,151
You choose.

682
00:37:59,945 --> 00:38:02,405
Right now.

683
00:38:02,447 --> 00:38:04,741
Either way, it
proves me right, huh?

684
00:38:04,783 --> 00:38:08,286
Either way,
it's exactly like
I told you.

685
00:38:08,327 --> 00:38:11,915
Everyone around you,
everything you touch dies.

686
00:38:29,307 --> 00:38:31,350
William, come here,
come here!

687
00:38:31,392 --> 00:38:33,394
Hey! Are you OK?
Are you all right?

688
00:38:33,436 --> 00:38:35,354
Are you all right?
Did he hurt you?
You all right? OK.

689
00:38:35,396 --> 00:38:36,648
He's gonna be fine.

690
00:38:36,689 --> 00:38:39,192
Don't you talk
to him!

691
00:38:39,234 --> 00:38:40,819
Don't even look at him!

692
00:38:43,655 --> 00:38:47,325
[Line ringing]

693
00:38:47,366 --> 00:38:48,493
Moira:<i>Hello?</i>

694
00:38:50,578 --> 00:38:54,207
<i>Hello? Who is this?</i>

695
00:38:54,249 --> 00:38:55,959
Mom, it's...

696
00:38:56,001 --> 00:38:57,877
it's Oliver.

697
00:39:00,379 --> 00:39:03,675
My son has been dead
for 5 years.

698
00:39:03,716 --> 00:39:05,343
Please don't call
here again.

699
00:39:05,384 --> 00:39:08,554
<i>Mom, Mom, please
just listen to my voice.</i>

700
00:39:15,312 --> 00:39:17,981
It's Oliver.

701
00:39:18,023 --> 00:39:19,149
<i>I did not die
on the Gambit.</i>

702
00:39:19,191 --> 00:39:22,360
<i>I'm alive. I'm OK.</i>

703
00:39:22,401 --> 00:39:23,945
Oliver?

704
00:39:25,613 --> 00:39:27,157
Oliver,
is that you?

705
00:39:27,199 --> 00:39:28,325
Yeah, Mom, it's me.

706
00:39:28,366 --> 00:39:29,701
Just please don't
hang up, OK?

707
00:39:29,742 --> 00:39:34,164
Oh, no. No, no, no.
I won't.

708
00:39:34,206 --> 00:39:37,125
<i>Oh, my beautiful boy.</i>

709
00:39:37,167 --> 00:39:40,295
Is...is your father
a-alive?

710
00:39:45,967 --> 00:39:47,219
No.

711
00:39:49,470 --> 00:39:53,183
No. He...he
and, um...

712
00:39:53,225 --> 00:39:55,060
and Sara didn't
make it.

713
00:39:58,897 --> 00:40:00,857
Oliver...

714
00:40:00,899 --> 00:40:05,362
sweetheart, I can't
imagine what you've
been through.

715
00:40:05,403 --> 00:40:08,323
<i>W-where are you?</i>

716
00:40:08,365 --> 00:40:11,243
I...I'm not
entirely sure,

717
00:40:11,284 --> 00:40:12,577
but I'm...

718
00:40:14,495 --> 00:40:17,082
I'm...I'm on a boat.

719
00:40:17,123 --> 00:40:19,792
I love you, and...

720
00:40:19,834 --> 00:40:22,461
and I'm coming
home, OK?

721
00:40:22,503 --> 00:40:26,091
Ohh! I love you!

722
00:40:26,132 --> 00:40:28,885
<i>Oh, Oliver,
I love you so much.</i>

723
00:40:30,636 --> 00:40:33,056
Adrian: You won.

724
00:40:33,098 --> 00:40:36,851
Your son has
his father back,

725
00:40:36,893 --> 00:40:41,147
and he learned
exactly who
his father was

726
00:40:41,189 --> 00:40:43,191
just like you
learned

727
00:40:43,233 --> 00:40:45,693
who your father was
right here...

728
00:40:47,737 --> 00:40:50,156
on these very same
waters.

729
00:40:50,198 --> 00:40:51,199
What?

730
00:40:51,241 --> 00:40:52,909
William's younger
than you were,

731
00:40:52,951 --> 00:40:54,744
so he's gonna be fine,

732
00:40:54,786 --> 00:40:55,828
you know...

733
00:40:58,706 --> 00:41:00,792
and you have
each other...

734
00:41:00,833 --> 00:41:02,627
What are you saying?

735
00:41:02,668 --> 00:41:05,171
which is good.

736
00:41:05,213 --> 00:41:07,840
Oliver, that's good

737
00:41:07,882 --> 00:41:10,551
because it's gonna
be lonely...

738
00:41:13,430 --> 00:41:15,932
without Mom

739
00:41:15,974 --> 00:41:17,809
and Felicity.

740
00:41:17,850 --> 00:41:19,227
No, Adrian!

741
00:41:19,269 --> 00:41:23,815
[Gunshot]

742
00:41:23,856 --> 00:41:27,944
[Explosions]

743
00:41:44,169 --> 00:41:46,338
[Explosions continue]

744
00:42:08,193 --> 00:42:09,319
Man: Greg, move your head.

